  "local_port": 51848,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you get good letters of recommendation?",
  "response": "Acquiring strong letters of recommendation is crucial for applications to academic programs, scholarships, and job opportunities. Here are some strategies to help you obtain impactful recommendations:\n\n1. **Choose the Right Recommenders:**\n   - Select individuals who know you well and can speak positively about your skills, work ethic, and character. Professors, mentors, supervisors, and colleagues are often good choices.\n   - Preferably, choose recommenders who have a strong reputation or hold significant positions within your field.\n\n2. **Build Strong Relationships:**\n   - Show genuine interest in the courses or projects you are involved in.\n   - Participate actively and contribute meaningfully.\n   - Regularly communicate with your potential recommenders and seek feedback on your performance.\n\n3. **Be Professional and Courteous:**\n   - Ask for recommendations well in advance of the deadline. A typical lead time is at least 4-6 weeks.\n   - Ensure your request is polite and respectful. \n\n4. **Provide Supporting Information:**\n   - Share your resume, transcript, and any relevant accomplishments.\n   - Provide a summary of what you hope to achieve and why you need the recommendation.\n   - Highlight specific projects or experiences that you want the recommender to mention.\n\n5. **Clarify the Purpose:**\n   - Let your recommender know why you are asking them specifically and how their insight is valuable for your application.\n   - Explain the criteria or qualities that the institution or employer is looking for.\n\n6. **Guidance and Support:**\n   - Offer to meet and discuss the recommendation request in more detail.\n   - Provide examples of what you would like them to mention or emphasize.\n   - Remind them of deadlines and confirm the submission process.\n\n7. **Follow-Up:**\n   - Express gratitude and appreciation for their support.\n   - After submitting your application, keep them updated on your progress and outcomes.\n\nRemember, a well-prepared approach and respect for your recommender\u2019s time can significantly enhance the quality of your recommendation letters.",
